
The laundry bill is getting quite expensive. And we're not talking about the dirty laundry unveiled in Minnesota this week with the so-called Love Boat scandal. The glut of penalties in the league was on a record-setting pace before last weekend, when officials reportedly called 246 penalties. Things got so out of control that the NFL found itself slapping major fines on players for bumping referees, both intentionally and unintentionally. 

